		<hr class="show-hr1">	
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1 show-map" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Germany_in_Europe.svg/1401px-Germany_in_Europe.svg.png">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Federal Republic of Germany is a country located in Central and Western Europe sharing borders with many countries. Ancient humans inhabited this area more than 600,000 years ago. During the more modern ages, the area was inhabited by the Germanic tribes for many centuries. The Germanic tribes became a part of the Frankish Empire under Charlemagne. Later on, Germany became a part of the Holy Roman Empire, headed by Charlemagne as the first King.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				After the death of Emperor Frederick II in 1250, Germany broke into many tribes. In 1517 after Martin Luther published his 95 Thesis, the Protestant Reformation began. Almost all the countries in Europe were involved in the wars between the Catholics and the newly formed Protestants. Protestant Reformation war known as “The Thirty Year Wars” (1618-1648) was mostly fought in Germany resulting in 20% of Germans being killed. After the Thirty Years War, the Kingdom of Prussia was established in Germany.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/d2/f1/05/d2f1056beb460f98fe29672a19b3771b.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Martin Luther hanging his 95 Theses</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				In 1871 after defeating France in Franco-Prussian War, the German states were unified under the new parliament called the Reichstag. Germany made a triple alliance with Austria and Italy. In 1914 World War I started with Germany and its allies including the Ottomans against much of Europe as well as the United States. After the defeat of Germany in 1918 the Versailles Treaty was signed redrawing the Germany’s border leaving Germany in internal conflict and economic crises.

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img2" src="https://42796r1ctbz645bo223zkcdl-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/DTgcRAF9JT8.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Germany formed the axis powers of the first world war with Austria and Italy</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Austrian born young Adolf Hitler created the Nazi party and became the Chancellor of Germany in 1933, later declared himself the Fuhrer. In 1939 Hitler started the second World War by invading Poland. He invaded much of Europe including France, however Britain, the United States and the Allies was able to defeat Hitler.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/7/2007/06/GettyImages-545920327-99769fd.jpg?quality=90&resize=620%2C413">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Adolf Hitler led Germany into war with the allies during the massive second world war</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Germany’s defeat and Hitler’s death led to Germany’s division into two countries East and West Germany with a wall built in Berlin. East Germany was under the communist rule of Soviet Union, while West Germany was a free market state. With the fall of communist Soviet Union, the Berlin Wall was taken down in 1989 and in 1990 Germany was united into one country.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://news.artnet.com/app/news-upload/2020/04/GettyImages-1181070865-1024x683.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Berlin Wall divided Germany into two territories</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today Germany is a federal parliamentary republic led by a chancellor. It is the strongest economic power in Europe leading in global industries and
technological sectors. Germany is a highly developed high income country offering its citizens social security, universal health-care and tuition free university education. Germany is a member of United Nations, NATO, and the European Union.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically Germany has sandy coasts on the North and Baltic seas. Central and South Germany is mountainous with highest mountain points in the South in the Bavarian Alps. The Rhine river winds down in the West, the Elbe in the East, and the Danube in the South. The climate in the North is oceanic with cool summers and mild winters, and cold and snowy in the Alps region.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://lp-cms-production.imgix.net/features/2016/01/bavarian-alps-1500-cs.jpg?auto=compress&fit=crop&fm=auto&sharp=10&vib=20&w=1200&h=800">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Bavarian Alps, Germany</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Germany historically has been called the “the land of the poets and thinkers” because of the effects of its writers and philosophers role in Europe. It has been one of the most forward thinking countries in Europe in ancient and modern times. One of the country’s greatest writer and thinker was Johann Wolfgang von Goethe(1749-1832). His drama Faust I tells the legendary story of a scholar who makes a deal with the Devil to get unlimited powers in exchange of his soul. Goethe’s work is considered the greatest German literature.
Johann Gutenberg’s invention off the moveable press machine in 1450s made it possible to print books on a mass scale allowed the entire world to read books (the very first being the Bible) rather than only a privileged few.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://cdn.britannica.com/70/74370-050-07DC0A6E/artist-visualization-workshop-proof-Johannes-Gutenberg-sheet.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Johann Gutenberg invented the first mobile printing press, forever changing the world of literature</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				German classical music was created by the most well known composers like Johann Sebastian Bach, Georg Friedrich Handel, Ludwig von Beethoven, Felix Mendelssohn, and Richard Wagner.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.mediastorehouse.com/p/617/germany-berlin-johann-sebastian-bach-playing-9503801.jpg.webp">
