		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about Germany
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				“Mad” King Ludvig (1845-86) was a former monarch in German’s Bavarian State. He built the famous Neuschwanstein Castle in 1892 which is an icon of Bavaria and the inspirations behind Cinderalla’s Castle in Disney.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://cdn1.matadornetwork.com/blogs/1/2011/05/germany-1200x853.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>The Neuschwanstein Castle was constructed in honor of German composer Richard Wagner</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
	
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Brothers Jacob and Wilhelm Grimm, were academics and authors who studied in the University of Marburg. Their lifelong dedication to research of the German language, literatures and folktale led them to compile the stories and publish them. Their method of collecting the folklore stories became the basis of folklore studies. Their classic collection Children and Household Tales of almost 200 stories was first published in 1812. Some of the stories in this book were “Cinderella”, “Beauty and the Beast”, “Snow White”, “Three Little Pigs”, “Little Riding Hood”, and “Sleeping Beauty”.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
